U.K. stocks climbed, erasing an
earlier retreat as shares of Autonomy Corp. and Man Group Plc
advanced.  The FTSE 100 Index gained 0.3 percent to 5,720.23 at 11:31
a.m. in London after earlier falling as much 0.3 percent.  Autonomy gained 3 percent to 1,289 pence and Man Group
increased 2.4 percent to 270.4 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
